            g. earning and other remuneration of personnel engaged from aboard in connection with an investment. 2. The transfers referred to in subsection (1) shall be subjected to any payments, dues, fees, levies or any other similar obligation that is due in terms of such laws or regulations. The amount permitted for transfer under   this section shall be the balance after deduction of the financial obligations referred to herein. 3. The market rate of exchange published by the Central Bank of Sri Lanka prevailing on the date of transfer shall be applicable for the purpose of this section and in the absence of a market for foreign exchange, the rate to be used shall be the most recent exchange rate for the conversions of currencies into Special Drawing Rights. 4.

